problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/continuous-subarray-sum/description/

Intuition
In this problem to find subarray which are divisible with an integer k , what we can do is at any index i calculate the current prefix sum at that index : total , total is in form of kx + y , where y is the remainder , if we find any previous prefix sum which has same remainder y , which can be in form kz + y , then the remaining subarray will be kx +y - (kz+y) = k(x-z) hence sum of subarrays between the two prefix sum will be divisble by k , but we need to find if there exists any subarray with length >= 2 which is divisible by k , so we use hash map as database to store the first occurence of that remainder becasue it maximizes the distance betwen indices giving greater chance of finding a subarray whose length is at least two, if that remainder occurs again then we can calculate the length of subarray with its current index - the occurence at previous index .

Approach
we create an empty hashmap , which stores the indexes of remainders at their first occurence , initally remainder 0 occus at index -1 meaning when subaaray was empty , initally total = 0 for an empty subarray hence remiander will be zero for 0 % k , hence hashmap[0] = -1,

reaverse the array ,
at every index total += nums[i]
remainder = total % k
check if remainder in hash map if yes : find difference of current index - previous index >= 2 if true return True else continue

if remainder not in hash map , thaen index i will be its first occurence hence update i in hash map for remainder ,

if array is completly traversed and no such subarray is found which is divisble by k and has len >= 2 then return false

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def checkSubarraySum(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> bool:
        total = 0
        remainder_to_index = {}
        remainder_to_index[0] = -1
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            total += nums[i]
            remainder = total % k
            if remainder  in remainder_to_index:
                if i - remainder_to_index[remainder] >= 2:
                    return True
            else:
                remainder_to_index[remainder] = i
                
        return False
